  "prompt": "What are de broghlie matter wave?",
  "response": "De Broglie matter waves, proposed by Louis de Broglie in 1924, are a fundamental concept in quantum mechanics that describes the wave-like properties of matter. Here are the key points:\n\n1. Basic Concept\n- Every particle has an associated wavelength\n- Matter can exhibit wave-like characteristics\n- This wave-particle duality applies to all matter, not just light\n\n2. De Broglie Wavelength Equation\n\u03bb = h/p\nWhere:\n- \u03bb = wavelength\n- h = Planck's constant (6.626 \u00d7 10^-34 J\u00b7s)\n- p = momentum of the particle\n\n3. Key Characteristics\n- Wavelength is inversely proportional to momentum\n- More massive/faster particles have shorter wavelengths\n- Wavelength becomes significant for very small particles like electrons\n\n4. Experimental Confirmation\n- Electron diffraction experiments\n- Neutron diffraction\n- Confirmation of wave-like behavior of matter\n\n5. Significance\n- Fundamental to quantum mechanics\n- Explains wave-like behavior of particles\n- Basis for understanding quantum phenomena\n\nThe concept revolutionized understanding of particle physics and quantum mechanics.",
